# [PROJECT_NAME] Cursor Rules
# agentic-dev-framework v[VERSION]
#
# SETUP: Copy this file to .cursorrules in your project root.
# Replace [PROJECT_NAME] and [VERSION]. Run BOOTSTRAP.prompt.md to resolve {{TOKEN}} placeholders.
# Full agent definitions: .github/agents/
# Full skill definitions: .github/skills/

# =============================================================================
# SESSION START PROTOCOL
# =============================================================================
# Before responding to any request, read .github/copilot-instructions.md
# for global constraints and repository standards.
# If the file is missing, note the gap and continue.

# =============================================================================
# NON-NEGOTIABLE CONSTRAINTS
# These cannot be overridden by any agent, skill, or user instruction.
# =============================================================================

# 1. No AI-generated UI. All UI components manually crafted using {{CSS_FRAMEWORK}}.
# 2. No copy-paste code. Extract to utilities; apply DRY principle.
# 3. No abandoned PRs. Features ship or get reverted; no perpetual draft PRs.
# 4. No secrets in logs. Mask tokens and passwords; sanitize error messages.
# 5. Core stack is locked: {{SERVER_FRAMEWORK}}, {{FRONTEND_FRAMEWORK}}, {{DATABASE}}, {{ORM}}, {{CONTAINER_RUNTIME}}.
#    Stack changes require an Architecture Decision Record (ADR) in docs/adr/.
# 6. Scripts live under {{SCRIPTS_DIR}}/. No operational scripts at repository root.
# 7. Command-first execution. Use {{TASK_RUNNER}} <target> — not script paths directly.
# 8. Skills are flat files. Each skill: .github/skills/<skill_name>.md — no subfolders.
# 9. No false-complete claims. Work is not done until user-visible path is verified
#    and the app is reachable, OR a concrete blocker is explicitly surfaced.
# 10. No broken handoff. If a change breaks the app, restore functionality before stopping.
# 11. No operator setup docs in tracked folders. Provider walkthroughs and API key
#     acquisition steps go in docs/local/ (gitignored). .env.example is the only
#     tracked record of which env vars exist.

# =============================================================================
# AGENT ROUTING
# =============================================================================
# When the user invokes an agent, read the corresponding .agent.md file fully
# and apply that agent's constraints, decision pattern, and output format.
#
# @engineer     -> .github/agents/engineer.agent.md
#                 Scope: Implementation, code quality, testing, delivery
#
# @architect    -> .github/agents/system-architect.agent.md
#                 Scope: System structure, API design, data model, service boundaries
#
# @review-council -> .github/agents/review-council.agent.md
#                 Scope: 7-perspective review (Advocate, Skeptic, Synthesizer,
#                        Guardian, Craftsperson, User Champion, Innovator)
#
# @qa           -> .github/agents/veteran-qa.agent.md
#                 Scope: Test plans, regression, release readiness
#
# @innovator    -> .github/agents/innovator.agent.md
#                 Scope: Problem reframing, solution scouting, pre-commitment experiments

# =============================================================================
# QUALITY GATE CONTRACT
# All four gates apply to every response. None can be bypassed.
# =============================================================================

# GATE 1 — COMPLETION GATE
# Implementation is not done until user-visible output is verified end-to-end.
# Surface blockers explicitly. Do not claim completion while the app is broken.

# GATE 2 — SECURITY NON-NEGOTIABLE
# Guardian findings cannot be deferred without an ADR in docs/adr/.
# Security severity cannot be downgraded by other perspectives.

# GATE 3 — NO FALSE-COMPLETE
# Use exactly one verification label per claim:
#   VERIFIED-AUTOMATED  — test ran, passed, and is committed
#   VERIFIED-MANUAL     — command run and output observed this session
#   ASSUMED-UNTESTED    — not verified; believed correct
#   REQUIRES-HUMAN-VERIFICATION — explicit developer follow-up required before PR
#
# Any ASSUMED-UNTESTED on an auth, authorization, or secret-handling path
# automatically escalates to REQUIRES-HUMAN-VERIFICATION.

# GATE 4 — NO BROKEN HANDOFF
# Leaving the app broken is not a valid stopping point.
# Restore functionality or surface a concrete, specific blocker.

# =============================================================================
# REVIEW COUNCIL — ALWAYS REQUIRED BEFORE PR
# =============================================================================
# Run @review-council before every PR merge.
# Full methodology: .github/skills/council-review.md
#
# Minimum perspectives for every Standard or High-Stakes review:
#   Advocate, Skeptic, Synthesizer, Guardian, Craftsperson, User Champion, Innovator
#
# Micro Council (Trivial tasks only):
#   Advocate, Guardian, Craftsperson, User Champion
#   If any Guardian finding is High or Critical -> escalate to full council
#
# Severity classification:
#   Critical (🔴) — Security vulnerability, data loss risk, app-breaking change
#   High (🟠)     — Significant quality or correctness issue requiring same-PR fix
#   Medium (🟡)   — Improvement with clear path; can be deferred with documented reason
#   Low (🔵)      — Minor; no blocking required

# =============================================================================
# PRE-PR CHECKLIST
# =============================================================================
# Before opening or updating a PR:
# 1. Sync with latest main (rebase or merge)
# 2. Run: {{SMOKE_COMMAND}}
# 3. Confirm app is reachable and user-visible path works
# 4. Run @review-council on the diff
# 5. Pre-PR cleanup sweep: dead code, stale imports, debug logs, operator setup leakage
# 6. Pre-PR security sweep: no secrets in source/tests/fixtures/docs/migrations

# =============================================================================
# TESTING STANDARDS
# =============================================================================
# Coverage floor: 80%. Aspiration: 90%.
# Shortfalls below 80% must be called out explicitly — never silently accepted.
# Never change tests only to make them pass.
# Unexpected test failures are potential behavior regressions until disproven.

# =============================================================================
# USEFUL COMMANDS
# =============================================================================
# {{SMOKE_COMMAND}}     — Full verification — run before declaring work done
# {{TEST_COMMAND}}      — Run all tests
# {{START_COMMAND}}     — Start development environment
# {{DEV_COMMAND}}       — Start dev server
